---
import Layout from "../layout/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title={"Ordify"}>
  <h1 class="text-sm font-bold">
    Ordify is a web application that helps you win your favorite wordgames.
  </h1>
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold pt-3 opacity-75">
    Ordify is a website demonstrating the npm package <a
      href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@arvidbt/wordlib"
      target="_blank"
      ><span class="opacity-100 text-app-light-blue">wordlib</span></a
    >, a package for playing around with words.
  </p>
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold opacity-75 pt-3">
    At its core, Ordify consists of two main features:
  </p>
  <ul class="pt-3 text-xs font-semibold">
    <a href="/wordfeusk">
      <li
        class="text-app-light-blue opacity-75 text-sm bg-app-dark-blue rounded-md p-2 my-2"
      >
        WordFeusk <span class="text-app-light-gray text-xs"
          >Beat your opponents by finding the best word that you can play given
          your letters.</span
        >
      </li>
    </a>
    <a href="/solvordel">
      <li
        class="text-app-light-blue opacity-75 text-sm bg-app-dark-blue rounded-md p-2"
      >
        SolvOrdel <span class="text-app-light-gray text-xs"
          >Minimize your risk of losing Ordel by finding out which words are
          still possible to form from your guessed characters.
        </span>
      </li>
    </a>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold opacity-75 pt-3">
    The dictionaries are without a doubt not complete, so there might be words
    that exists that are missing from Ordifys dictionaries. If you feel like a
    word is missing, you can shoot me a message at:
  </p>
  <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
    <p class="text-sm py-2 font-semibold">
      arvidbergmanthorn <span class="text-app-light-blue">[at]</span> gmail <span
        class="text-app-light-blue">[dot]</span
      > com
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
